node.text:
Visit @SculptMovements 💕 for workouts, routine, and everythin else you eed to become fit! .
Treino de MMI com 01. Agachamento máquina 15/12/10 + drop com extensora 4 x 4 / 4x3 / 4x2 /4x 1 aumentando a carga ( 1 série ) 
1 x 10 com pico de contração em cima + 10 saindo da inércia 
1 x 10 com excêntrica lenta + 10 concêntrica lenta + 10 
02. Stiff 3 x 15 + bom dia 10 
03. Flexora 9 x 6 alternando a carga entre leva e pesado 
1 x 30 curtas + 10 isometria + 12 
1 x unilateral 8 /7/6 até zerar sem intervalo 
04. Flexora em pé 3 x 12 parando no meio + glúteo no cabo 3 x 12 
Panturrilhas sempre 😅
Macacão @santtaloren
.
.
.
Credit @graoficial #Fitness #fitfam #fitspo #motivation #workout #workoutvideo #legday #gym #abs

node.text:
1.7 STONE DIFFERENCE (10.7kg up in 26 weeks)⁣

Visit @GymGlutes 💕 for workouts, routine, and everythin else you eed to become fit!

⁣
Before I ramble on I just wanted to say thank you!! Thank you all for supporting my journey. I am so happy I can help so many of you on your journeys and to normalise weight gain♥️⁣
⁣
Measurements: ⁣
Height - 5 ft 10⁣
Waist - 30 inches⁣
Glutes - 43 inches⁣
Weight - in the picture☺️⁣
⁣
3800 calories ⁣
No cardio⁣
⁣
Another week ticked off and as you guys know it’s been harder these past few weeks with some negative comments BUT that’s what fuels me even more to my goals! ⁣
⁣
I’m around 17 weeks (4 months) away from starting prep for 2021 which is crazyyyy to think about but that’s 17 weeks to push myself harder in this bulk!⁣
⁣
2 weeks isolating has meant home training but I’m still working and adapting around the situation! I’ll be back in the gym next Thursday and I cannot wait😭 ⁣
⁣
Ready to smash another week💪🏻⁣
.
.
.
Credit: @gljfitnessuk #abworkout #coreworkout #quadsworkout #legworkout #gluteworkout #workoutvideos  #gymmotivation #bodybuilding #fitnessmotivation #homeworkout #fullbodyworkout #bodyweightworkout

node.text:
Queen of grabbing weights that are too heavy for me 👑 

Credit @anaofit rrr

Full Body Kettlebell Circuit! Visit @GymGlutes 💕 for workouts, routine, and everythin else you eed to become fit!
-
-
Don’t Forget to Double Tap & Save for Later 💪🏻
-

-
3 circuits of: 
1️⃣Kettlebell Swings 11
2️⃣ Kettlebell Deadlift to Squat 10
3️⃣ Single Leg RDL to Arm Row 8-10
4️⃣ Plank Pull Through 12
5️⃣ Sit Ups to Overhead Press 10
-

-
Song: Surface- Sunday Best remix 

Credit @bethyred

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Sculpt Lifestyle on September 05, 2021. May be an image of one or more people, people standing and text that says 'Me + Me my period'.

node.text:
🎈 PERIOD BLOAT 🎈Or let’s talk birth control. I was put on hormonal contraception when I was 14. 

Follow us (@GymGlutes) for the best daily workout tips 💪

I stayed on it for over 10 years. 

As a teen, it was to calm the extreme pain of my periods.

Later it was to keep my ex-partner happy; even though I wanted to be done with the stuff, he preferred birth control to anything else. 

These days I don’t take hormonal contraception. 

And after so many years of not having one, I’m fascinated by my period. 

My body BLOATS massively and RETAINS allll the WATER. 

My lower tummy swells. Aches. For a good 12 hours every cycle, I have extremely bad cramps and nausea. And then I become peaceful, sleepy, calm. 

It all feels, in its own way, powerful. Even as my body changes - or maybe because it does. 

So today, here, I just want to remind you:

It’s ok if your body fluctuates throughout the month. 

It’s ok if you don’t bloat one day and bloat like a beautiful balloon the next. 

It’s ok if you choose to use hormonal contraception. It’s equally ok if you choose not to. Just make sure that decision is yours and yours alone. 

It’s ok if you honour your body and listen to your body in a way that serves you. 

It’s ok if you do you. 

Period puffy or bloaty belly or in any way at all. 

You got this, you marvellous human. 
.
.
.
.
